<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="@color/white"
    android:orientation="vertical">


    <ImageView
        android:id="@+id/awareness"
        android:layout_width="35dp"
        android:layout_height="35dp"
        android:layout_gravity="right"
        android:layout_margin="30dp"
        android:padding="20px"
        android:src="@drawable/cancel" />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="30dp"
        android:text="Treatment"
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:textStyle="bold |italic" />

    <androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_marginStart="30dp"
        android:layout_marginEnd="30dp"
        android:layout_marginBottom="20dp">

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_gravity="center"
            android:textColor="@color/black"
            android:text="Types of Eating Disorder Treatment
The severity of the eating disorder and any co-occurring disorders will determine the initial treatment level you or your loved one should pursue. The following are the common levels and types of eating disorder treatment, in order of acuity:
\n\n1)     Outpatient Treatment [Seeing a Therapist / Counselor]
\n\n2)     Intensive Outpatient Treatment [IOP]
\n\n3)     Residential Treatment
\n\n4)     Inpatient / Hospital Treatment"
            android:textSize="18sp" />
    </androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>


</LinearLayout>